How do I afford to travel so much? It‚Äôs one of the most frequently asked questions that I get, and one that I think is important to answer often!
Most people assume that I earn my living from Instagram, but I actually make very little from brand partnerships etc. One of my passions is jewelry making, and I started my shop @spiritnectar back in 2014. It has changed a lot since then, and I branched out into selling crystals and gemstones too. The shop takes up 90% of my time, and that wee little bit of spare time that I have is used for travel!
From behind the screen it‚Äôs easy to assume that many of us live a lavish lifestyle, but so many of us with large social media accounts work regular jobs with long hours. I take a lot of photos when I do get out to places, so I will often circulate through a huge collection of older pictures which can make it look like I‚Äôm always traveling. In reality, I don‚Äôt get out all that much and I‚Äôm always greeted by a massive pile of work when I get back! üôà Anyways, just wanted to share some realness üíú‚ò∫Ô∏è
